  "texts": [
    "This connection is explored in the recent works of Arroyo-Rabasa and Bouchitté [5] and, independently, the paper of the author jointly with Bate, Caputo, Valentine and Wald [8].",
    "Similar connection is also explored in the work of De Pauw [38].Finally, there is the somewhat surprising connection of the prescribed Jacobian equation to large-scale geometry.",
    "This was first observed independently by Burago and Kleiner [11] and McMullen [33] and is of particular interest to our work.",
    "Recall that Z ⊂ R d is a separated net, if there are two constants ε > 0 and δ > 0 such that for any x ∈ R d, there is z ∈ Z with ∥x -z∥ ≤ ε and whenever z, w ∈ Z, z ̸ = w, then ∥z -w∥ ≥ δ. Burago and Kleiner show that existence of biLipschitz solutions (i.e.",
    "Lipschitz, injective solutions, with Lipschitz inverses) to (1.1) given a right hand side ρ ∈ L ∞ (Q), corresponds to the existence of biLipschitz bijectionsF: Z → Z d, where Z is a separated net.They continue to show that there exists ρ ∈ L ∞ (Q), which, moreover, only attains two positive values, such that there is no biLipschitz solution to (1.1)."
  ],
